cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new approach to interpreting deep learning models. It also involves the use of mutual information, which is a common concept in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category as the paper focuses on information flow in neural networks. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possibility as deep learning is commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper uses network science to explore information flow in deep learning models.
